## Attribute Types

### String Attributes (Double and Single Quotes)

<Button label="Click Me" theme='dark' />

### String Escaping (Backslash and Alternate Quotes)

<Tooltip text="She said \"hello\"" />
<Tooltip text='It\'s a beautiful day' />
<Tooltip text='She said "hello"' />

### Primitive Attributes (Numbers, Booleans, Null)

<Pagination activePage={2} isInteractive={true} showArrows={false} ref={null} />
<Slider min={-3.14} max={2.5e10} step={0.01} />

### Boolean Shorthand

<Input disabled />
<Checkbox checked required />

### JSON Object Attributes

<Chart config={{
  "type": "bar",
  "title": "Monthly Revenue",
  "data": [10, 20, 30, 40],
  "options": {
    "legend": true,
    "animate": false
  }
}} />

### JSON Array Attributes

<TagList items={{["alpha", "beta", "gamma"]}} />

<DataGrid rows={{[
  {"id": 1, "name": "Alice"},
  {"id": 2, "name": "Bob"}
]}} />

### Variable Attributes

<Button label={$frontmatter.buttonText} />
<Heading level={$config.heading_level} />

### Mixed Attributes on a Single Component

<DataTable
  title="User List"
  page={1}
  sortable
  columns={{["Name", "Email", "Role"]}}
  onSort={$handlers.sort_users}
/>

## Variable Interpolation

The current document title is **{$title}** (version {$version}).

Nested paths work too: {$config.theme_name}.

## Escaping

Literal variable syntax: \{$not_a_variable}

Literal double braces: \{{ and \}}

Literal single brace: \{

Literal backslash: \\

## Code Constructs (No Interpolation)

Variables inside inline code are literal: `{$title}` renders as-is.

Fenced code blocks are also literal:

```rdx
<Badge status="beta" active={true}>New Feature</Badge>
{$this_is_not_interpolated}
```

```ts
const x: number = 42;
// {$also_not_interpolated}
```

